1.2: A delayed callback that pegs to the next animation frame instead of a user configurable timeout.
A ConditionalDelay object invokes the associated function after a specified interval delay and checks its return value.
Debouncer will perform a specified action exactly once for any sequence of signals fired repeatedly so long as they are fired less than a specified interval apart (in milliseconds).
A Deferred represents the result of an asynchronous operation.
Constructs an object that waits on the results of multiple asynchronous operations and marshals the results.
A Delay object invokes the associated function after a specified delay.
Throttle will perform an action that is passed in no more than once per interval (specified in milliseconds).
